      "source": [
        "### Resampling-Correction for Logistic Regression\n",
        "\n",
        "When a logistic regression is trained on resampled data, the resampling changes the class prior seen by the model. If the resampling is only class-based (for example, random undersampling or random oversampling) and does not otherwise change the conditional feature distributions $P(X \\mid Y=1)$ and $P(X \\mid Y=0)$, the slope coefficients can still be used, but the intercept must be shifted back to the original training-set class prior.\n",
        "\n",
        "Let\n",
        "\n",
        "-   $\\hat p_\\text{pop}$ = `phat_pop`, the fraud rate in the overall training set before resampling.\n",
        "-   $\\hat p_\\text{resampled}$ = `phat_resampled`, the fraud rate in the training set after resampling.\n",
        "-   $\\widehat{\\alpha}_\\text{resampled}$ = `intercept_hat_resampled`, the intercept from a logistic regression trained on the resampled data.\n",
        "-   $\\widehat{\\beta}_\\text{resampled}$ = the slope vector from the same resampled logistic regression.\n",
        "\n",
        "The fitted log-odds from the resampled model are\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\widehat{\\text{logodds}}_\\text{resampled}(x)\n",
        "=\n",
        "\\widehat{\\alpha}_\\text{resampled}\n",
        "+\n",
        "x^\\top \\widehat{\\beta}_\\text{resampled}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Under class-based resampling,\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\text{odds}_\\text{pop}(x)\n",
        "=\n",
        "\\text{odds}_\\text{resampled}(x)\n",
        "\\cdot\n",
        "\\frac{\\hat p_\\text{pop}/(1-\\hat p_\\text{pop})}\n",
        "     {\\hat p_\\text{resampled}/(1-\\hat p_\\text{resampled})}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Taking logs gives the corrected log-odds:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\widehat{\\text{logodds}}_\\text{corrected}(x)\n",
        "=\n",
        "\\widehat{\\text{logodds}}_\\text{resampled}(x)\n",
        "+\n",
        "\\log\\left(\\frac{\\hat p_\\text{pop}}{1-\\hat p_\\text{pop}}\\right)\n",
        "-\n",
        "\\log\\left(\\frac{\\hat p_\\text{resampled}}{1-\\hat p_\\text{resampled}}\\right).\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Equivalently, only the intercept changes:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\widehat{\\alpha}_\\text{corrected}\n",
        "=\n",
        "\\widehat{\\alpha}_\\text{resampled}\n",
        "+\n",
        "\\operatorname{logit}(\\hat p_\\text{pop})\n",
        "-\n",
        "\\operatorname{logit}(\\hat p_\\text{resampled}),\n",
        "\\qquad\n",
        "\\widehat{\\beta}_\\text{corrected}\n",
        "=\n",
        "\\widehat{\\beta}_\\text{resampled}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The corrected fitted probability is\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\widehat{P}_\\text{corrected}(Y=1 \\mid X=x)\n",
        "=\n",
        "\\frac{1}{1+\\exp\\{-\\widehat{\\text{logodds}}_\\text{corrected}(x)\\}}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "For fraud data, $\\hat p_\\text{pop}$ is usually much smaller than $\\hat p_\\text{resampled}$. Therefore the correction term is usually negative, lowering the intercept and pulling predicted probabilities back toward the true population fraud rate."
      ],
      "id": "5524dc45"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: resampling-logistic-intercept-correction\n",
        "\n",
        "%matplotlib inline\n",
        "\n",
        "def logit(p):\n",
        "    p = np.clip(p, 1e-12, 1 - 1e-12)\n",
        "    return np.log(p / (1 - p))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Example: correct the intercept of a logistic regression trained on the RUS data.\n",
        "# The same formula applies to any class-based resampled logistic regression.\n",
        "logistic_rus = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, solver=\"lbfgs\")\n",
        "logistic_rus.fit(X_train_rus, y_train_rus)\n",
        "\n",
        "phat_pop = y_train.mean()\n",
        "phat_resampled = y_train_rus.mean()\n",
        "intercept_hat_resampled = logistic_rus.intercept_[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "intercept_correction = logit(phat_pop) - logit(phat_resampled)\n",
        "intercept_hat_corrected = intercept_hat_resampled + intercept_correction\n",
        "\n",
        "# decision_function uses the resampled intercept. Add the same intercept correction\n",
        "# to get log-odds on the original training-set class-prior scale.\n",
        "logodds_hat_resampled = logistic_rus.decision_function(X_test)\n",
        "logodds_hat_corrected = logodds_hat_resampled + intercept_correction\n",
        "phat_uncorrected = logistic_rus.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]\n",
        "phat_corrected = 1 / (1 + np.exp(-logodds_hat_corrected))\n",
        "\n",
        "display(pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "    \"phat_pop\": [phat_pop],\n",
        "    \"phat_resampled\": [phat_resampled],\n",
        "    \"intercept_hat_resampled\": [intercept_hat_resampled],\n",
        "    \"intercept_correction\": [intercept_correction],\n",
        "    \"intercept_hat_corrected\": [intercept_hat_corrected],\n",
        "    \"mean_uncorrected_test_probability\": [phat_uncorrected.mean()],\n",
        "    \"mean_corrected_test_probability\": [phat_corrected.mean()]\n",
        "}))\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 6))\n",
        "CalibrationDisplay.from_predictions(\n",
        "    y_true=y_test,\n",
        "    y_prob=phat_uncorrected,\n",
        "    n_bins=20,\n",
